0:12:34,2 --> 0:12:36,124
"Hermes" is an ion engine ship.


379
0:12:36,124 --> 0:12:38,54
And for those of you who don't
know what ion engines are--


380
0:12:38,54 --> 0:12:41,64
I mean, I described it
briefly in the chapter--


381
0:12:41,64 --> 0:12:43,864
but basically, instead
of a chemical propellant


382
0:12:43,864 --> 0:12:45,53
going out the back
of the ship providing


383
0:12:45,53 --> 0:12:48,34
a large amount of impulse,
it's a very small amount


384
0:12:48,34 --> 0:12:50,45
of acceleration caused
by magnetic fields


385
0:12:50,45 --> 0:12:52,37
throwing ions out
the back of the ship.


386
0:12:52,37 --> 0:12:54,6
Now the benefit to
this is that you


387
0:12:54,6 --> 0:12:57,19
can have much, much,
much less reactant mass.


388
0:12:57,19 --> 0:12:59,97
And I believe-- and this is
just my own subjective opinion--


389
0:12:59,97 --> 0:13:3,476
we have to improve on the
technology that we have


390
0:13:3,476 --> 0:13:4,6
and just keep working that.


391
0:13:4,6 --> 0:13:5,975
I think that's
the only way we'll


392
0:13:5,975 --> 0:13:9,92
be able to send humans long
distances out into space.


393
0:13:9,92 --> 0:13:12,52
The amount of
chemical propellant


394
0:13:12,52 --> 0:13:14,83
