something big enough


395
0:13:14,83 --> 0:13:17,89
to support humans for
several months out to Mars


396
0:13:17,89 --> 0:13:19,78
would just be huge, huge.


397
0:13:19,78 --> 0:13:21,7
I mean, you'd be putting
millions and millions


398
0:13:21,7 --> 0:13:24,67
of kilograms of just fuel
into space to do this.


399
0:13:24,67 --> 0:13:27,69
So you need to
minimize how much you


400
0:13:27,69 --> 0:13:29,93
launch from Earth to
make that efficient.


401
0:13:29,93 --> 0:13:32,81
So that means for "Hermes,"
I decided, oh, OK,


402
0:13:32,81 --> 0:13:35,4
so it's got a slow constant
acceleration from ion engines.


403
0:13:35,4 --> 0:13:36,78
It's got a nuclear
reactor aboard


404
0:13:36,78 --> 0:13:39,47
